column1: Gross domestic product (GDP), total (2017 PPP $ billions)

Definition: Sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes and minus any subsidies not included in the value of the products, expressed in 2017 international dollars using purchasing power parity (PPP) rates.
Source: World Bank (2020a). World Development Indicators database. Washington, DC. http://data.worldbank.org. Accessed 22 July 2020.

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development
